Lost Lands: Mahjong is an Interesting game with many puzzles to solve. I can recommend it to anyone who wants to kill some time or needs to relax, since the atmosphere in the game offers this possibility.

Pros:
- Many different puzzles;
- The story line isn't fabulous but a great addition to the game still;
- Atmospheric sounds during puzzles are relaxing and let's one forget about time (even the puzzle time limit ;) );
- For a free game, the graphics are nice. In comparison to other games they are okay;
- It's free to play.

Cons:
- Tutorial is rather short and the learning curve is achieved through some (minor) form of trial and error;
- Game can become repetitive when sites need revisiting (many times) for items which are gained by sheer coincidence;
- Progression is partially gained by using real money, but since it's a free game and the developers need to make money from it somehow, this will be subject to interpretation as whether it be a con or not.

All in all I like this game and since it's free, anyone can give it a try to see if (s)he likes it or not. For those who like Mahjong, this game can (and probably will) offer many hours of fun and relaxation.
